              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 18pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Symbol, serif">&#183;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Diluted
      EPS&#160;increased&#160;12.8 percent to
$1.41</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">H&#220;NENBERG, Switzerland &#8211; February 11,
2009 &#8211; </font>Alcon, Inc. (NYSE:ACL) reported global sales of $1,497.5 million
for the fourth quarter of 2008, an increase of 1.9 percent compared to the
fourth quarter of 2007, or 7.1 percent excluding the impact of foreign exchange
fluctuations. Acquisition revenue contributed growth of 0.7 percent, resulting
in an organic growth rate of 6.4 percent. Net earnings for the fourth quarter of
2008 increased 12.5 percent to $423.6 million, or $1.41 per share on a diluted
basis, compared to $376.5 million, or $1.25 per share on a diluted basis for the
fourth quarter of 2007.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">For the
full year 2008, Alcon, Inc. reported global sales of $6,293.7 million, an
increase of 12.4 percent over 2007 global sales of $5,599.6 million, or 9.5
percent excluding the impact of foreign exchange fluctuations. Acquisition
revenue contributed growth of 1.2 percent, resulting in an organic growth rate
of 8.3 percent. Net earnings for 2008 rose 29.0 percent to $2,046.5 million, or
$6.79 per share on a diluted basis compared to $1,586.4 million or $5.25 per
share on a diluted basis for the full year 2007. Results for 2008 included a
$235.7 million reduction in taxes related to an agreement with the Internal
Revenue Service regarding the company&#8217;s investment in and advances to the former
Summit Autonomous, Inc. Excluding this tax benefit, net earnings for the full
year 2008 would have been $1,810.8 million or $6.00 per diluted share. Results
for 2007 included an after tax charge of $20.8 million related to the impairment
of Alcon&#8217;s refractive assets.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Reconciliations
of reported and adjusted results for the full year are included in the financial
tables below.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff">-more-</font></font></div><br>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
</font></div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
</font></div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;
</font></div>
        </div>
      </div><br>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#8220;I am
pleased to report that Alcon again delivered solid financial results for the
fourth quarter and full year of 2008, and did so in a challenging business
environment, which accelerated in the fourth quarter. The long term strategic
drivers of our business remain in place, supported by the favorable demographics
of the eye care industry and our demonstrated ability to gain market share,&#8221;
said Cary Rayment, Alcon&#8217;s chairman, president and chief executive officer. &#8220;In
response to the environment we expect to face in 2009, we will prioritize
spending on research and development and market development activities that
drive future growth, while implementing actions to reduce our overall cost
structure.&#8221;</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#8220;Furthermore,
our solid performance in 2008 demonstrated that Alcon continues to make progress
against its strategic imperatives even in the current challenging business
environment,&#8221; said Rayment. &#8220;More importantly, I believe that as the economy
recovers and currency rates stabilize, Alcon should strengthen sales growth and
continue to deliver profitability well above the industry average.&#8221;</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 9.1pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Fourth
Quarter Sales Review</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Highlights
of sales for the fourth&#160;quarter of 2008&#160;are provided
below.&#160;Unless otherwise noted, all comparisons are versus the
fourth&#160;quarter of 2007.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Wingdings">&#216;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">International
      sales rose 1.2 percent to $832.3 million, or 10.4 percent excluding
      foreign exchange, with sales in emerging markets increasing 3.0 percent,
      or 16.4 percent excluding the impact of foreign exchange. Sales in the
      United States increased 2.8 percent to $665.2
  million.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Wingdings">&#216;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Pharmaceutical
      sales of $578.1 million&#160;were flat in the quarter, but&#160;grew 4.8
      percent on a constant currency basis.&#160;Outside the U.S., Alcon
      reported solid growth with pharmaceutical sales rising 10.9 percent in
      constant currency.&#160;U.S. pharmaceutical sales were negatively affected
      by a decline in prescription volumes for the U.S. ophthalmic
      market.&#160;Despite the slowdown in the U.S. market, the company saw its
      pharmaceutical market shares rise on a global basis, led by the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;
      </font>family of products (including <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">, TRAVATAN Z</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">DuoTrav</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">TM</font>
      ophthalmic solutions). Total <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      family sales rose 11.3 percent in the quarter, while combined sales of
      <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TRAVATAN Z</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>&#160;and<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> DuoTrav</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">TM</font>
      ophthalmic solutions increased 57.7 percent. Economic and seasonal factors
      had a negative impact on global sales of allergy products, which fell 12.7
      percent. Alcon&#8217;s flagship allergy products, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Pat</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">anol</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Pat</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">aday</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#8482;</font> ophthalmic solutions,
      increased their combined U.S.&#160;market share from 73.5 to 77.8 percent
      during the quarter.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>

        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">

                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Surgical
      sales of $723.2 million rose 3.2 percent, or 8.5 percent on a constant
      currency basis.&#160;Unit growth of 6.5 percent for <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font>intraocular lenses
      continued to exceed the estimated global growth rate of cataract
      procedures.&#160;Increased market penetration of the company&#8217;s advanced
      technology monofocal and multifocal IOLs continued to contribute to growth
      in IOL sales.&#160;Combined sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> IQ</font>&#160;and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySo</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">f</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> Natural</font>&#160;lenses
      rose 12.2 percent in the quarter, while combined sales of the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> Toric</font> and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> ReSTOR</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Aspheric</font>
      lenses&#160;increased&#160;27.8 percent.&#160;Unit sales of cataract
      systems increased 4.1 percent in the quarter, which reflects the continued
      success of the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Infiniti</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font>vision system with
      the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">OZil</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font>torsional hand
      piece&#160;and the launch of the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Laureate</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      phacoemulsification system in multiple markets outside
  the</font></div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Highlights
of earnings for the fourth quarter of 2008&#160;are provided
below.&#160;Unless&#160;otherwise noted, all comparisons are versus the fourth
quarter of 2007.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">

              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Gross
      profit&#160;margin of 79.2 percent reflected an increase&#160;of
      4.5&#160;percentage points, much of which was due to a temporary impact on
      cost of goods sold of the sharp devaluation of most foreign currencies
      against the U.S. dollar.</font></div>

                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Selling,
      general and administrative expenses increased 1.7 percent, which reflected
      cost control actions taken by management to reduce and prioritize spending
      in the face of the challenging economic environment.&#160;Alcon&#8217;s captive
      insurance company settled claims against the third parties for damages
      incurred prior to 2006 at one of Alcon&#8217;s sales and distribution
      facilities.</font></div>
              </td>

              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Research
      and development expenses (excluding in-process R&amp;D in 2007) decreased
      1.6 percent to $157.4 million, or 10.5 percent of sales.&#160;The decline
      in R&amp;D expenses was primarily due to several milestone payments made
      in 2007 and differences in timing of costs associated with regulatory
      filings and clinical studies between the two periods.&#160;The company
      also incurred $9.3 million of in-process R&amp;D costs in the fourth
      quarter of 2007 associated with the WaveLight
  acquisition.</font></div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">New
Product and R&amp;D Pipeline Update</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Summarized

      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Wingdings">&#216;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">On
      February 5, 2009, the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">IQ Toric</font> intraocular
      lens was approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA). The
      <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">IQ Toric</font> lens combines
      aspheric optics found in the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> IQ</font> and the astigmatic
      correction of the existing <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Toric</font>
    lens.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Wingdings">&#216;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The
      <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> ReSTOR</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">+</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">3.0</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> Add</font> was approved by the
      FDA on December 23, 2008. This lens, which corrects for presbyopia in
      patients with cataracts, was launched outside the United States in
      September 2008 and will be launched in the United States in the first
      quarter of 2009.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Wingdings">&#216;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">On
      December 2, 2008 the company announced that the European Medicines
      Evaluation Agency (EMEA) formally approved <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Azarga</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      ophthalmic suspension. The fixed combination eye drop is used as an
      adjunct treatment for elevated intraocular pressure (IOP) associated with
      open-angle glaucoma or ocular
hypertension.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt;" face="Wingdings">&#216;&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The
      <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">CONSTELLATION</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      vitrectomy system was launched at the American&#160;Academy of
      Ophthalmology in November of 2008. The new system enhances precision and
      efficiency for the surgeon and safety for the
  patient.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>

              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Riverplate
      Biotechnology, Inc., a subsidiary of Lantibio, Inc. advised the company
      that it has filed a new drug application (NDA) with the FDA for its sodium
      hyaluronate dry eye treatment. Alcon has licensed the U.S. marketing
      rights to this product, although Riverplate Biothechnology, Inc. is
      responsible for the clinical development of the
  compound.</font></div>
              </td>

                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon
      submitted to the FDA and received approval of its Investigational New Drug
      Application to permit the commencement of human trials of the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Aganocide</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      molecule, NVC-422. Alcon has licensed the rights to the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Aganocide</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      compounds from NovaBay Pharmaceuticals, Inc. for the treatment of eye, ear
      and sinus infections and for use in contact lens
  solutions.</font></div>
              </td>

      approved <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TRAVATAN
      Z</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;
      </font>ophthalmic solution. The company commenced the launch of this
      product in Canada in January 2009.</font></div>

              </td>

                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The
      company has not yet gained FDA approval of its new formulation of a fixed
      combination of tobramycin and dexamethazone, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">ST</font>,<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#160;</font>although the FDA
      continues to review the application. On January 2, 2009, a competitor
      launched a generic version of the company&#8217;s <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: super">&#174;</font>
      ophthalmic suspension, and Alcon launched its own
  generic.</font></div>
              </td>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Financial
Guidance</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">In light
of the current dynamics in the marketplace, the company expects 2009 organic
sales growth (excluding currency and acquisitions) to be in the mid-single
digits. The company also expects that organic sales growth in the first half of
the year is likely to be at the low end of this range due to the current
challenging economic and market environment. The company also projects diluted
earnings per share on a U.S. GAAP basis to be between $6.00 and $6.20 and on an
adjusted basis (excluding restructuring charges) to be between $6.05&#160;and
$6.25.</font></div>

                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">On
      January 8, 2009, Alcon announced that Kevin Buehler will become president
      and chief executive officer of the company on April 1, 2009. Cary Rayment
      will retire as president and chief executive officer on March 31, 2009,
      but will continue to serve on the board as Alcon&#8217;s non-executive chairman
      of the board. Mr. Buehler will also be nominated for election to the board
      of directors at the Annual General Meeting on May 5, 2009 in Zug,

                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">In
      its ongoing quest to maintain a world class organization, the company has
      initiated programs to align its operations with the evolving economic and
      market environment. These programs include a staffing reduction that will
      result in a pre-tax charge of approximately $21 million, the majority of
      which will be incurred in the first quarter of 2009. The staffing
      reduction is expected to deliver ongoing annualized savings of
      approximately $40 million beginning in the second quarter, with the full
      effect realized in the second half of
2009.</font></div>

Description</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon,
Inc. is the world&#8217;s leading eye care company, with sales of $6.3 billion in
2008.&#160;Alcon, which has been dedicated to the ophthalmic industry for more
than&#160;60 years, researches, develops, manufactures and markets
pharmaceuticals, surgical equipment and devices, contact lens care solutions and
other vision care products that treat diseases, disorders and other conditions
of the eye.&#160;Alcon&#8217;s majority shareholder is Nestl&#233;, S.A., the world&#8217;s
largest food company.&#160;All trademarks noted in this release are the property
of Alcon, Inc. For more information about Alcon, visit
www.alcon.com.</font></div>

Meaningful</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 10.25pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Note:<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font>Percent Change in Constant
Currency calculates sales growth without the impact of foreign exchange
fluctuations. Management believes constant currency sales growth is an important
measure of the company&#8217;s operations because it provides investors with a clearer
picture of the core rate of sales growth due to changes in unit volumes and
local currency prices.&#160;&#160;This measure is considered a non-GAAP
financial measure as defined by Regulation G promulgated by the U.S. Securities
and Exchange Commission.&#160;&#160;Certain reclassifications have been made to
prior year amounts to conform with current year presentation.</font></div><br>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 10.25pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 10.25pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">N/M - Not
Meaningful</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 10.25pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Note:<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font>Percent Change in Constant
Currency calculates sales growth without the impact of foreign exchange
fluctuations. Management believes constant currency sales growth is an important
measure of the company&#8217;s operations because it provides investors with a clearer
picture of the core rate of sales growth due to changes in unit volumes and
local currency prices.&#160;&#160;This measure is considered a non-GAAP
financial measure as defined by Regulation G promulgated by the U.S. Securities
and Exchange Commission.&#160;&#160;Certain reclassifications have been made to
prior year amounts to conform with current year presentation.</font></div><br>

Adjusted net earnings and diluted EPS measure the results of the company's
operations without certain items that pertained only to the period presented.
Management believes these measures are an important measure of the company&#8217;s
operations because it provides investors with a clearer picture of the core
operations of the company.&#160;&#160;This measure is considered a non-GAAP
financial measure as defined by Regulation G promulgated by the U.S. Securities

      </font></td>
                <td align="left" nowrap valign="bottom" width="1%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2px"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">)</font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td align="left" valign="bottom" width="76%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4px">
                  <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 12.55pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">2008
      organic sales growth</font></div>
                </td>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 13.7pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 12.55pt"><br></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 11.4pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Note:
Constant currency sales growth rates calculate sales growth without the impact
of foreign exchange fluctuations. Organic sales growth rates calculate sales
growth without the impact of foreign exchange and acquisition fluctuations.
Management believes constant currency sales growth and organic sales growth are
important measures of the company&#8217;s operations because they provide investors
with a clearer picture of the core rates of sales growth attributable to changes
in unit volumes and local currency prices and, with respect to organic sales
growth, excluding the effect of acquisitions.&#160;&#160;These measures are
considered non-GAAP financial measures as defined by Regulation G promulgated by
the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.</font></div>
